# Royal Mix Global — SECURITY HARDENING CHECKLIST (v1.0)

This document tracks critical security tasks required to reach 2000% Production-Ready Architecture.

---

## 1. HTTPS / SSL Enforcement
- [ ] Enable HSTS (HTTP Strict Transport Security)
- [ ] Redirect all HTTP → HTTPS on reverse-proxy
- [ ] Add SSL certificate (Cloudflare Full/strict)
- [ ] Add secure headers using Helmet

## 2. Database Encryption
- [ ] Hash passwords using bcrypt (saltRounds=12+)
- [ ] Encrypt sensitive fields using AES-256-GCM
- [ ] Mask sensitive data in logs
- [ ] Add automatic database backup encryption

## 3. Secrets Management
- [ ] Move all secrets to .env.production
- [ ] Enable GitHub Actions encrypted secrets
- [ ] Add .env to .gitignore
- [ ] Add secret rotation policy (monthly)

## 4. Firewall, WAF, DDoS Protection
- [ ] Enable Cloudflare WAF rules
- [ ] Configure DDoS protection
- [ ] Add bot traffic detection
- [ ] Add country blocking for known attack zones

## 5. Advanced Rate Limiting
- [ ] Add per-IP strict rate limit
- [ ] Add per-route limits with different thresholds
- [ ] Add Redis-based persistent throttling
- [ ] Add device fingerprinting + ban list

## 6. Backend Payment Verification (Pi Network)
- [ ] Verify server-side callback signatures
- [ ] Reject non-matching payment hashes
- [ ] Log all failed attempts with IP + device ID
- [ ] Create transaction audit trail

## 7. Error Handling, Logging, Monitoring
- [ ] Add Winston logger (security level)
- [ ] Add request ID tracking (correlation ID)
- [ ] Add uptime monitoring (UptimeRobot)
- [ ] Add Sentry for crash/error reporting

---

## Status Summary
Security Level: **Phase 1 — HARDENING**
Progress: Initial structure created. Pending implementation steps.

